draw plots and data graphs: gnuplot
copy a disk bit-a-bit: dcfldd if=/dev/sourcedrive hash=md5,sha256 hashwindow=10G md5log=md5.txt sha256log=sha256.txt hashconv=after bs=512 conv=noerror,sync split=10G splitformat=aa of=driveimage.dd
play all files in a directory: find | xargs -i mplayer {}
If you need to know where your variables are allocated (heap or stack) in go: go run -gcflags -m main.go
record desktop: recordmydesktop --device pulse --s_quality 0 --v_quality 8 --on-the-fly-encoding
